evaluation.response:
It's fascinating how the body can adapt to pain and discomfort. Going through intense situations for extended periods of time can indeed numb your senses over time. It's a coping mechanism that the mind and body use to manage stress and prevent feelings from becoming overwhelming.&#x20;

This doesn't mean the pain isn't real or it won't have negative effects. Chronic pain and long-term sleep deprivation can have serious medical consequences in the long run, such as hormonal changes, fatigue, depression, digestive issues, and even suppression of the immune system. Therefore, it's important to find solutions to the root causes of the pain instead of relying on the body's ability to numb it.&#x20;

If you ever need assistance or just someone to talk to, don't hesitate to reach out.
